aniBsuSuStatus.name: aniBsuSuStatus
aniBsuSuStatus.contactinfo: Postal: Aperto Networks Inc 1637 S Main Street Milpitas, California 95035 Tel: +1 408 719 9977
aniBsuSuStatus.description: This group allows the users of the BSU to access status information about the SU. It consists of 2 tables - The Upstream Link Status Table and Downstream Link Status Table.

aniBsuSuUSLinkStatusTable.name: aniBsuSuUSLinkStatusTable
aniBsuSuUSLinkStatusTable.description: This table accesses the upstream status attributes of each SU connected to this BSU.

aniBsuSuUSLinkStatusEntry.name: aniBsuSuUSLinkStatusEntry
aniBsuSuUSLinkStatusEntry.description: Upstream Status information for a single SU. An entry in this table exists for each SU that is connected to the BSU.

aniBsuSuStatusUSPolarization.name: aniBsuSuStatusUSPolarization
aniBsuSuStatusUSPolarization.description: The upstream Polarization. This field is used by SU to adjust the polarization selection when transmitting a burst to the BSU. Each SU has a single antenna which can be polarized either horizontally(1) or vertically(2).

aniBsuSuStatusUSModulation.name: aniBsuSuStatusUSModulation
aniBsuSuStatusUSModulation.description: The current upstream Modulation for this SU.

aniBsuSuStatusUSFec.name: aniBsuSuStatusUSFec
aniBsuSuStatusUSFec.description: The current upstream FEC method for this SU.

aniBsuSuStatusUSRxPower.name: aniBsuSuStatusUSRxPower
aniBsuSuStatusUSRxPower.description: The Upstream Receive Power. The value -130 is considered invalid.

aniBsuSuStatusSuTxPower.name: aniBsuSuStatusSuTxPower
aniBsuSuStatusSuTxPower.description: The Upstream SU Tx Power. The value -130 is considered invalid.

aniBsuSuDSLinkStatusTable.name: aniBsuSuDSLinkStatusTable
aniBsuSuDSLinkStatusTable.description: This table accesses the downstream status attributes of each SU connected to this BSU.

aniBsuSuDSLinkStatusEntry.name: aniBsuSuDSLinkStatusEntry
aniBsuSuDSLinkStatusEntry.description: Downstream Status information for a single SU. An entry in this table exists for each SU that is connected to the BSU.

aniBsuSuStatusDSPolarization.name: aniBsuSuStatusDSPolarization
aniBsuSuStatusDSPolarization.description: The downstream Polarization. This field is used by BSU to adjust the polarization selection when transmitting a burst to the SU. Each SU has a single antenna which can be polarized either horizontally(1) or vertically(2).

aniBsuSuStatusDSModulation.name: aniBsuSuStatusDSModulation
aniBsuSuStatusDSModulation.description: The current downstream Modulation for this SU.

aniBsuSuStatusDSFec.name: aniBsuSuStatusDSFec
aniBsuSuStatusDSFec.description: The current downstream FEC method for this SU.

aniBsuSuStatusDSRxPower.name: aniBsuSuStatusDSRxPower
aniBsuSuStatusDSRxPower.description: The Downstream Receive Power in dBm. It consists of 2 values, one for vertical polarization and one for horizontal polarization. It is displayed as 'vertical,horizontal' When nothing is being received, a value NA is displayed. Eg. for vertical = -20 and horizontal = NA, the agent will display '-20,NA'.

aniBsuSuStatusBsuTxPower.name: aniBsuSuStatusBsuTxPower
aniBsuSuStatusBsuTxPower.description: The BSU Tx Power for a particular SU.

aniBsuSuLinkStatusTable.name: aniBsuSuLinkStatusTable
aniBsuSuLinkStatusTable.description: This table accesses the other link status attributes of each SU connected to this BSU.

aniBsuSuLinkStatusEntry.name: aniBsuSuLinkStatusEntry
aniBsuSuLinkStatusEntry.description: Link Status information for a single SU. An entry in this table exists for each SU that is connected to the BSU.

aniBsuSuStatusPropagationDelay.name: aniBsuSuStatusPropagationDelay
aniBsuSuStatusPropagationDelay.description: The time taken to transmit a packet from BSU to SU (or vice versa) in microseconds.

aniBsuSuStatusDistance.name: aniBsuSuStatusDistance
aniBsuSuStatusDistance.description: The distance in meters between the BSU and SU.

aniBsuSuStatusLinkType.name: aniBsuSuStatusLinkType
aniBsuSuStatusLinkType.description: The link type for a particular SU.

aniBsuSuStatusPathLossExponent.name: aniBsuSuStatusPathLossExponent
aniBsuSuStatusPathLossExponent.description: The path loss exponent from BSU to SU
